Andrei Dostoevsky

  • son of Ivan (Goncharov) and Fyodor Dostoevsky
    • second oldest of his family
  • boy, cis
    • he/him
  • gay
  • starts the series at 12 and ends at 19
  • born February 21st, 2003
  • Namesake: Andrei Bely
  • Ability: Silver Dove of Petersburg
    • Ability Details: Silver Dove of Petersburg manifests as a singular silver dove, which can essentially be used as a tracking device, used to track down a single target whom the user wishes to kill. While the user has to do the killing themselves as the dove will not do it on its own and is no different morphologically from a normal dove, as long as the ability is active, the single target can be tracked down anywhere.
  • Affiliation: though he does end up joining the Apprentices of the ADA alongside his older sister, Anastasia Dostoevskaya, he's more loyal to the Gunslinger Kids out of both organizations.
  • Level at which I think about them: medium. He has a boyfriend, Stockton Montgomery who is owned by a friend of mine, and technically exists in a whole different universe, but since we know that cross-dimensional travel is at least plausibly canon in the BSD universe, that's not a problem for them.
  • Brief Notes:
    • A notoriously impatient boy, Andrei is the type of person who does not like to wait for anyone or anything, including himself, to be ready for something he wants to do. While he is and can easily be seen as pushy and demanding, he demands no more from others than what he does of himself, even if it pushes his body and mind to the very limit. Andrei has few friends, as he does not see the point in making them, but though he says this is fine by him and he prefers to be alone, in reality he is quite lonely, and would like some friends if he could only make them properly.
    • Andrei is incredibly intelligent; he excels mainly in math and math-related subjects, and is a polymath, having studied or currently studying mathematics, biology, chemistry, music, philosophy, and literature. By far, his favorite thing however is math and music; he learned how to play piano at an incredibly early age thanks to both of his fathers, and they further encouraged his instrument learning skills to the point where he can feasibly play most any instrument so long as he is given instruction. He is considered a musical prodigy, both in his home country and in Yokohama, and his skills rival that of Nobunori Nakajima-Akutagawa, who outranks him only slightly on stringed instruments. It is due to this that Andrei holds a grudge towards Nobunori, who, in his own words, could not care less.
    • Andrei goes to great lengths to please his fathers, though they are never demanding of him and will praise him for whatever accomplishments he achieves, and know how Andrei has a tendency to push himself. He is also a skilled poet, though his poetry trends on the dark side of subject materials. He is fascinated by the subject and study of entropy, and often makes choices in his life based on random number generators or by rolling a set of dice he keeps on him at all times and using them as a means of direction when he is unsure of what option to take. His range of success with this is fairly wide; at times it ends up helping him, though more often than not, it leads him into rather sticky situations he could have avoided if not for indecisiveness.
